            Integrated Utility Management
        </h2>
        <p class="text-slate-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg leading-relaxed" data-i18n="grid_dash_desc">
            Visualize substation health with thermal heat maps and real-time
            component status. Centralize all inspection reports and historical
            data in one platform.
        </p>

        <p class="text-slate-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg leading-relaxed"></p>
        <span data-i18n="grid_dash_long_desc">Substations concentrate high-voltage equipment — transformers, circuit breakers,
        insulators, busbars — in environments where access is restricted and failure
        consequences are severe. Inspection cycles that once took days of manual
        work now run in a single flight. The software captures thermal signatures
        across switchgear and transformer banks, identifying overheating connections
        and insulation degradation before they escalate. UV sensors detect partial
        discharge and corona activity on insulators and bushings — faults that are
        invisible to standard cameras but predictable weeks before failure. Structural
        checks on lattice towers, cross-arms, and perimeter fencing are logged automatically,
        with changes flagged against previous flights. Vegetation encroachment near
        high-voltage conductors is mapped and measured, not just noted. photoes of
        the substation gives maintenance teams accurate spatial data for retrofit
        planning and equipment positioning — without relying on outdated site drawings.
        On the analytics side, AI processes every image from every flight: cracked
        or contaminated insulators, corroded clamps, missing hardware, water accumulation
        in cable trenches. Reports are generated per asset, per zone, with defect
        severity ranked for maintenance scheduling. Autonomous flight routes run
        on set intervals, building an inspection record that supports both predictive
        maintenance and regulatory compliance documentation.</span>
